<title>USA: First Nationwide extends exchange offer.</title>
<headline>First Nationwide extends exchange offer.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Nationwide Holdings Inc said on Tuesday it extended its offer to holders of its $575 million restricted 10-5/8 percent senior subordinated notes due 2003 to exchange them for a like principal amount of its 10-5/8 senior subordinated exchange notes due 2003.</p>
<p>The extended offer expires at 5 p.m. Tuesday. First Nationwide said the exchange agent, the Bank of New York Co Inc, said 99 percent of the outstanding notes have already been tendered in the offer.</p>
<p>First Nationwide is the holding company for California Federal Bank.</p>
